com.github.katjahahn.parser

Class MemoryMappedPE

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.katjahahn.parser.MemoryMappedPE

  • public class MemoryMappedPE
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the PE file content as it is mapped to memory.

    The bytes are read from file only on request, making it possible to map large files. Only maps section bytes for now. No file headers.

      • physToVirtAddress

        public long physToVirtAddress(long physAddr)
        Returns the virtual offset for the given physical address, if it is within a mapping. Otherwise -1 is returned.

        Spits out a warning if several matching virtual addresses are found and returns the last one.

        Parameters:
        physAddr - physical address
        Returns:
        virtual address for physAddr, -1 if it does not exist

      • getBytesIntValue

        public int getBytesIntValue(long offset,
                            int length)
        Retrieves the integer value of the bytes in the memory mapped PE given by offset and length.

        The values are considered little endian.

        Length must be between 1 and 4 inclusive.

        Parameters:
        offset - the index to start reading the integer value from
        length - the number of bytes used to convert to int
        Returns:
        int value

      • getBytesLongValue

        public long getBytesLongValue(long offset,

        Retrieves the integer value of the bytes in the memory mapped PE given by offset and length.

        The values are considered little endian.

        Length must be between 1 and 8 inclusive.

        Parameters:

        length - the number of bytes used to convert to long
        Returns:
        long value
